snippet.textDisplay:
@carwow So you're telling me that that a AWD car with 400bhp on paper is making 355awhp?
Even at 409bhp that's only a 13% lose to put down 355whp at all fours! Most new RWD cars will lose 15-18% on average and I have seen new AWD cars lose over 25% through their drivetrain and across all four wheels.
This makes no sense to me, so a car with 355awhp/265awkw, DCT, an incredible launch control system and only weighing barely over 1500kg only runs a 12.5 🤔
My E46 M3 CS is only making 253rwkw/340rwhp with roughly 410bhp based of a 17% lose that we calculated from pre modded dyno runs, so they weren't just guessed or we used a rough baseline.
My M3 is also manual, weighs approx the same as the RS3. The M3 standard is 1495kg but I have a sun roof so would be pretty close to even. And I have no launch control or any of the new age electronics, and I managed a12.3 the first time taking the car out ( I do have a 4.10 diff though aswell which will obviously help but not the point here )

Btw I have raced both a RS3 and a RS5 from a roll and beat them both!
Only thing that makes these new Audis put up somewhat of a fight is because of their LC, roll racing and they are really quite pathetic.

So these numbers don't really add up to me something isn't right and I thought a RS3 would of been a lot closer to the 300awhp mark.

But then again I could be completely wrong!
Not trying to argue here just want a healthy discussion and hopefully I can learn a thing or two or help some one else.

Keep up the good work guys love the channel!

Respect from Australia

This makes no sense to me, so a car with 355awhp/265awkw, DCT, an incredible launch control system and only weighing barely over 1500kg only runs a 12.5 🤔
My E46 M3 CS is only making 253rwkw/340rwhp with roughly 410bhp based of a 17% lose that we calculated from pre modded dyno runs, so they weren't just guessed or we used a rough baseline.
My M3 is also manual, weighs approx the same as the RS3. The M3 standard is 1495kg but I have a sun roof so would be pretty close to even. And I have no launch control or any of the new age electronics, and I managed a12.3 the first time taking the car out ( I do have a 4.10 diff though aswell which will obviously help but not the point here )

Btw I have raced both a RS3 and a RS5 from a roll and beat them both!
Only thing that makes these new Audis put up somewhat of a fight is because of their LC, roll racing and they are really quite pathetic.

So these numbers don't really add up to me something isn't right and I thought a RS3 would of been a lot closer to the 300awhp mark.

But then again I could be completely wrong!
Not trying to argue here just want a healthy discussion and hopefully I can learn a thing or two or help some one else.

Keep up the good work guys love the channel!

Respect from Australia

snippet.textDisplay:
Too often I have trouble falling asleep, and I've tried anything from the classic counting of sheep to weird medicine from my doctor which made me numb to any kind of emotions for months. But thanks to this video I slept like a drunk baby last night - so I feel a deep sense of gratitude towards Mat and Yanni for lulling me to sleep with a video of two fridge-white Audi's competing on a track - and none of the many variables of track surface, driver weight, sunroof, different wheels and tires, older vs. newer car, gear changes, driver reaction times, equipment in the two cars, has there been done any other changes to the model in the last two years which doesn't have to do with WLTP.....etc, really seems to be taken into serious consideration.
I love Mat Watsons other videos - apart from the ones with Yanni because he appears arrogant, self absorbed and boasting an uncharming macho presence - but this one is terrific because it just doesn't get my pulse or curiosity going - and hence, I fall asleep.
So thanks! From now on I can hopefully fall asleep every night if I just remember to put this video on. ;)
I'm watching it now, good night...zzzz
